# tesa6240 (Tesa Etikett Etikettendrucker 6240, PAL) is a distinct romset (NOT a
# #define alias): the industrial label printer runs on SX-64 hardware but with
# its OWN bespoke firmware — a unique BASIC (tesa-basic.ud4), KERNAL
# (tesa-kernal.ud3) and character generator (tesa-char.ud1), all three carried
# by the split-set tesa6240.zip. Unlike the vip64 sibling, NONE of the three
# main ROMs are shared with the c64 parent. Only the PLA (906114-01.ue4) is
# byte-identical to c64's 906114-01.u17 — located by CRC32 in the parent c64.zip
# and repacked under the ue4 board-position name tesa6240 expects. The mixed-
# provenance sx64 / vip64 precedent. pal_sx replaces the iec8 default with the
# built-in sx1541 drive — built-in hardware, never removed: no -iec8 override,
# the sx1541 device romset ships and the internal drive is present, backing the
# Tesa firmware's on-screen DISKETTE function.
