# c232 (Commodore 232, PAL, prototype) — a pre-production 264-line prototype on
# the same TED/264 driver (src/mame/commodore/plus4.cpp, c16_state, machine
# config c232 — c16p with the RAM default raised to 32K). c232 is a CLONE of
# c264 (the Commodore 264 prototype parent); the config chain c232 -> c16p ->
# plus4p makes it a PAL machine. c232 has no ROM_SYSTEM_BIOS alternates — a
# self-contained romset. Its kernal 318004-01 (dbdc3319) is UNIQUE to c232 and,
# with the basic 318006-01 (74eaae87), is packed under the exact ROM_START( c232 )
# names in the split-set clone zip c232.zip; the 251641-02 PLA (83be2076) is
# byte-identical to the parent's and merges from c264.zip. Two src lines,
# obtain_member locates each member by CRC32 and renames the PLA to the
# ROM_START( c232 ) name 251641-02.u7 (from the parent's "251641-02"). Like the
# C16 it omits the 3-PLUS-1 function ROMs (ROM_START has no "function" region).
asset|c232|public|zip|roms/c232.zip
src|c232|zip|https://archive.org/download/mame-0.250-roms-split_202212/MAME%200.250%20ROMs%20(split)/c232.zip
src|c232|zip|https://archive.org/download/mame-0.250-roms-split_202212/MAME%200.250%20ROMs%20(split)/c264.zip
