mem|c232|318004-01.u5|dbdc3319|3c77caf72914c1c0a0875b3a7f6935cd30c54201|-
mem|c232|251641-02.u7|83be2076|a89b18b2261233443c933c8b4663b108e7630924|-

# v364 (Commodore V364, NTSC, prototype) — the LAST machine of the TED/264 driver
# (src/mame/commodore/plus4.cpp, c16_state, machine config v364). v364 is a CLONE
# of c264 (the Commodore 264 prototype parent); its config calls plus4n (the NTSC
# Plus/4 config) then adds the T6721A speech synthesiser — the V364 is the
# speaking 264-line prototype. v364 has no ROM_SYSTEM_BIOS alternates — a
# self-contained romset. Its kernal kern364p (84fd4f7a) and speech ROM
# spk3cc4.bin (5227c2ee) are UNIQUE to v364 and, with the basic 318006-01
# (74eaae87) and the full Plus/4 3-PLUS-1 function pair 317053-01/317054-01
# (4fd1d8cb/109de2fc), are packed under the exact ROM_START( v364 ) names (no
# .uXX suffix) in the split-set clone zip v364.zip; the 251641-02 PLA (83be2076)
# is byte-identical to the parent's and merges from c264.zip. Two src lines,
# obtain_member locates each member by CRC32.
asset|v364|public|zip|roms/v364.zip
src|v364|zip|https://archive.org/download/mame-0.250-roms-split_202212/MAME%200.250%20ROMs%20(split)/v364.zip
src|v364|zip|https://archive.org/download/mame-0.250-roms-split_202212/MAME%200.250%20ROMs%20(split)/c264.zip
